To enhance the existing PHP code to include the features you've described, we need to make several changes. Below is an updated version of the code with explanations for each change:

```php
<?php

if (elgg_is_active_plugin('shareit_ranking')) {

    $box_view = elgg_get_plugin_setting('view_riverbox', 'river_activity_3C');

    $user = elgg_get_logged_in_user_entity();

    $title = elgg_echo('river_activity_3C:ranking');

    $db_prefix = elgg_get_config('dbprefix');

    // Retrieve user-specific interests to personalize the ranking
    $user_interests = get_user_interests($user->guid);

    // Pagination parameters
    $page = get_input('page', 1);
    $items_per_page = 10;
    $offset = ($page - 1) * $items_per_page;

    // Retrieve paginated and personalized ranking
    $ranking = shareit_get_personalized_ranking($user_interests, $items_per_page, $offset);
    $ideas = array();
    foreach($ranking as $idea_guid){
        foreach (get_object_vars($idea_guid) as $idea => $iguid){
            $ideas[] = get_entity((int) $iguid);    
        }
    }

    elgg_push_context('widgets');
    $river_body = '';
    if (is_array($ideas)) {
        $river_body .= '<ul class="shareit-ranking" id="shareit-ranking-list" data-next-page="' . ($page + 1) . '">';
        foreach ($ideas as $idea) {
            $li = elgg_view_list_item($idea, $vars);
            if ($li) {
                if (elgg_instanceof($idea)) {
                    $id = "elgg-{$idea->getType()}-{$idea->getGUID()}";
                } else {
                    $id = "ranking-{$idea->getType()}-{$idea->id}";
                }
                $river_body .= "<li id=\"$id\" class=\"$item_class\">$li</li>";
            }
        }
        $river_body .= '</ul>';
    } else {
        // Error handling: Log the issue when the ranking list fails to load
        error_log("Failed to load the ranking list for user {$user->guid}");
    }
    elgg_pop_context();

    // AJAX-based dynamic loading script
    $river_body .= "<script>
        $(window).scroll(function() {
            if ($(window).scrollTop() >= $(document).height() - $(window).height() - 10) { // Added a buffer of 10px
                // Load next page of ranking list
                loadRankingList();
            }
        });

        function loadRankingList() {
            var nextPage = parseInt($('#shareit-ranking-list').data('next-page')) || 2;
            $.ajax({
                url: elgg.get_site_url() + 'ajax/view/ranking/list',
                data: {
                    page: nextPage
                },
                type: 'GET', // Specify the request type
                beforeSend: function() {
                    if ($('#shareit-ranking-list').data('loading')) {
                        return false; // Prevent multiple concurrent AJAX calls
                    }
                    $('#shareit-ranking-list').data('loading', true);
                },
                success: function(response) {
                    $('#shareit-ranking-list').append(response);
                    $('#shareit-ranking-list').data('next-page', nextPage + 1);
                },
                error: function() {
                    console.error('Failed to load more rankings.');
                },
                complete: function() {
                    $('#shareit-ranking-list').data('loading', false);
                }
            });
        }
    </script>";

    $river_body .= '<p style="text-align:right; margin:3px 3px;"><a href="'.elgg_get_site_url().'thewire/ranking"><b>'.elgg_echo('river_activity_3C:viewmore').'</b></a></p>';

    echo elgg_view_module($box_view, $title, $river_body);
}
```

Here are the changes and enhancements made to the code:

1. Removed the pagination controls since we are now loading more content dynamically and don't need traditional pagination links.

2. Added a `data-next-page` attribute to the `<ul>` element that holds the ranking list. This attribute will keep track of the next page number to load.

3. Updated the scroll event handler to check if the user has scrolled near the bottom of the page (with a buffer of 10 pixels) before triggering the AJAX call.

4. Added a `beforeSend` function to the AJAX call to prevent multiple concurrent AJAX requests. This function checks if there's already a loading process (`data-loading` attribute) and cancels the new request if necessary.

5. Added a `complete` function to the AJAX call to reset the `data-loading` attribute once the request is finished, allowing for new requests to be made.

6. Changed the `elgg_echo` calls to concatenate strings to `$river_body`. This is necessary because `elgg_echo` is used for language translation and output, not for building HTML content.

7. Added a `type: 'GET'` to the AJAX call to explicitly define the request method.

8. Fixed the `console.error` message in the AJAX error handler to provide a more descriptive error message.

9. Removed the pagination view since we are now using infinite scrolling.

With these changes, the ranking list should now load dynamically as the user scrolls down, and it will be personalized based on the viewer's interests. Error handling is also improved to prevent multiple AJAX calls at the same time and to log issues when the list fails to load.

